---

<BaseLayout title="Balance Overview" description="Comprehensive faction power rankings across troop skills, armor, and weapons">
  <div class="page-content mod-info">
    <nav class="breadcrumb"><a href="/mod-info">Mod Info</a> / Balance Overview</nav>
    <h1 class="page-title">Balance Overview</h1>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>The Balance Triangle</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Every faction in TAOM is balanced across <strong>three axes</strong>: troop skills, armor protection, and weapon damage.
        Factions strong in one axis are deliberately weaker in others, creating asymmetric but balanced gameplay.
        No faction dominates all three — except elves, who are <strong>intentionally elite</strong> and balanced by extreme rarity and cost.
      </p>
      <div class="triangle-visual">
        <div class="triangle-axis">
          <div class="axis-icon">&#9876;</div>
          <div class="axis-info">
            <strong>Troop Skills</strong>
            <span>Cultural modifiers to combat skills — affects hit chance, block ability, and movement speed</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="triangle-axis">
          <div class="axis-icon">&#128737;</div>
          <div class="axis-info">
            <strong>Armor Protection</strong>
            <span>Cultural protection bonuses and weight multipliers — affects damage taken and mobility</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="triangle-axis">
          <div class="axis-icon">&#9876;</div>
          <div class="axis-info">
            <strong>Weapon Damage</strong>
            <span>Cultural damage_factor modifiers — affects raw damage output per hit</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Faction Power Comparison</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Grades reflect relative strength within each axis. <strong>S</strong> = dominant, <strong>A</strong> = strong, <strong>B</strong> = solid, <strong>C</strong> = below average, <strong>D</strong> = weak.
        See individual balancing pages for detailed numbers.
      </p>
      <div class="table-wrapper">
        <table class="power-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Culture</th>
              <th>Race</th>
              <th class="grade-col">Troops</th>
              <th class="grade-col">Armor</th>
              <th class="grade-col">Weapons</th>
              <th class="detail-col">Key Strength</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            {cultures.map(c => (
              <tr>
                <td class="culture-cell" style={`border-left: 3px solid ${c.color}`}>
                  <span style={`color: ${c.color}`}>{c.name}</span>
                </td>
                <td class="race-cell">{c.race}</td>
                <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade" style={`color: ${gradeColors[c.troops.grade]}`}>{c.troops.grade}</span></td>
                <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade" style={`color: ${gradeColors[c.armor.grade]}`}>{c.armor.grade}</span></td>
                <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade" style={`color: ${gradeColors[c.weapons.grade]}`}>{c.weapons.grade}</span></td>
                <td class="detail-cell">{c.troops.detail}</td>
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="elven-note">
        <h3>* Elven Factions <span class="elven-subtitle">— intentionally elite, balanced by rarity and cost</span></h3>
        <p class="section-desc">
          Elven factions operate on a different power scale. Their troops have +25 to +50 skill bonuses, the best armor in the game,
          and a -20% weapon modifier to compensate. They are balanced by <strong>extremely low population</strong>, high recruitment costs,
          and slow replenishment — not by statistical parity with other factions.
        </p>
        <div class="table-wrapper">
          <table class="power-table elven-table">
            <thead>
              <tr>
                <th>Culture</th>
                <th class="grade-col">Troops</th>
                <th class="grade-col">Armor</th>
                <th class="grade-col">Weapons</th>
                <th class="detail-col">Key Strength</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              {elvenCultures.map(c => (
                <tr>
                  <td class="culture-cell" style={`border-left: 3px solid ${c.color}`}>
                    <span style={`color: ${c.color}`}>{c.name} *</span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade" style={`color: ${gradeColors[c.troops.grade]}`}>{c.troops.grade}</span></td>
                  <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade" style={`color: ${gradeColors[c.armor.grade]}`}>{c.armor.grade}</span></td>
                  <td class="grade-cell"><span class="grade" style={`color: ${gradeColors[c.weapons.grade]}`}>{c.weapons.grade}</span></td>
                  <td class="detail-cell">{c.troops.detail}</td>
                </tr>
              ))}
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Infantry Power Rankings</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Ranked by combined melee skill bonuses (1H, 2H, Polearm), Athletics, armor protection, and weapon damage.
        Elven factions would rank S+ across the board but are excluded — they are balanced by population, not by stats.
      </p>
      <p class="section-desc coming-soon">
        Infantry subcategories coming soon: <strong>Front Line</strong> (shield wall), <strong>Shock Troops</strong> (charge damage),
        <strong>Line Breakers</strong> (anti-armor), <strong>Skirmishers</strong> (javelin/throwing).
      </p>
      {infantryTiers.map(t => (
        <div class="tier-row">
          <div class="tier-label" style={`background: ${t.color}25; border: 1px solid ${t.color}50; color: ${t.color}`}>
            <span class="tier-letter">{t.tier}</span>
            <span class="tier-desc">{t.label}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-cultures">
            {t.cultures.map(c => (
              <div class="tier-culture" style={`border-left: 3px solid ${c.color}`}>
                <strong style={`color: ${c.color}`}>{c.name}</strong>
                <span class="tier-reason">{c.reason}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Cavalry Power Rankings</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Ranked by Riding skill, Polearm/OneHanded combat, armor weight (lighter = faster mounts), and weapon damage.
        Includes both traditional cavalry and warg/beast riders where applicable.
      </p>
      {cavalryTiers.map(t => (
        <div class="tier-row">
          <div class="tier-label" style={`background: ${t.color}25; border: 1px solid ${t.color}50; color: ${t.color}`}>
            <span class="tier-letter">{t.tier}</span>
            <span class="tier-desc">{t.label}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-cultures">
            {t.cultures.map(c => (
              <div class="tier-culture" style={`border-left: 3px solid ${c.color}`}>
                <strong style={`color: ${c.color}`}>{c.name}</strong>
                <span class="tier-reason">{c.reason}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Ranged Power Rankings</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Ranked by Bow, Crossbow, and Throwing skill bonuses, armor weight (mobility for kiting), and relevant weapon damage.
        Elven factions would dominate — Mirkwood has +50 Bow, Rivendell +40 Bow, Lothlorien +35 Bow.
      </p>
      {archerTiers.map(t => (
        <div class="tier-row">
          <div class="tier-label" style={`background: ${t.color}25; border: 1px solid ${t.color}50; color: ${t.color}`}>
            <span class="tier-letter">{t.tier}</span>
            <span class="tier-desc">{t.label}</span>
          </div>
          <div class="tier-cultures">
            {t.cultures.map(c => (
              <div class="tier-culture" style={`border-left: 3px solid ${c.color}`}>
                <strong style={`color: ${c.color}`}>{c.name}</strong>
                <span class="tier-reason">{c.reason}</span>
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </section>

    <section class="info-section">
      <h2>Detailed Balancing Pages</h2>
      <div class="links-grid">
        <a href="/mod-info/troop-balancing" class="link-card" style="--lc-color: rgba(180, 120, 200, 0.35)">
          <strong>Troop Balancing</strong>
          <span>Cultural skill modifiers, baseline tables, and troop progression for all 16 cultures</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/mod-info/armour-balancing" class="link-card" style="--lc-color: rgba(200, 160, 100, 0.35)">
          <strong>Armour Balancing</strong>
          <span>Protection bonuses, weight multipliers, and tier breakdowns across 17 cultures</span>
        </a>
        <a href="/mod-info/weapon-balancing" class="link-card" style="--lc-color: rgba(220, 130, 130, 0.35)">
          <strong>Weapon Balancing</strong>
          <span>Damage analysis from TaleWorlds physics, cultural modifiers, and per-weapon breakdowns</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .mod-info {
    max-width: 1200px;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .breadcrumb a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  .breadcrumb a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

  .info-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .info-section h2 {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(212, 162, 76, 0.3);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .section-desc {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .coming-soon {
    background: rgba(212, 162, 76, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(212, 162, 76, 0.2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  /* Triangle visual */
  .triangle-visual {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .triangle-axis {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .axis-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .axis-info strong {
    display: block;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
